short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Navigate through commit history on GitHub using arrow keys

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: You know.. sometimes I just want to stalk how other people built some project from scratch, just revisit the initial commit, and enjoy the art of the project getting mature time by time. And i was a bit lazy to clone the repo and also was a bit lazy to browse commits one by one. So yes this is for lazy people who want to enjoy the art of committing history -- enjoy!
